Root `AGENTS.md` hard rules apply. Read the nearest scoped `AGENTS.md` and canonical `testing` and `tests-authoring` skills.

Verify repository identity, owner-local module and underscore paths, and edit-marker requirements before changing inherited test files. Do not add redundant owner markers inside owner-local paths.

Use existing owner-local test infrastructure. Verify symbol access and project references. Do not create duplicate test projects, fixtures, CI steps, MSBuild targets, or `module.yml` entries.

For locale and culture tests, treat `en-US` as structural truth. Verify `ru-RU` keys, attributes, variables, selectors, relative file paths, ordered positions, fallback, persistence, repeated switching, and cleanup.

Run exact canonical commands, preserve failures, never edit SPDX metadata, and never weaken assertions for green CI.
